 in the Humanities to the Rescue book series, a public humanities project dedicated to discussing the role of the arts and humanities today, Resonances against Fascism takes its cue from the disruptive force of music in traversing the boundaries between—and engaging readers from—modernist and avant-garde studies, critical and cultural theory, musicology and sound studies, critical race and gender studies, performance studies, and philosophy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aAvant-garde (Aesthetics) 0aFascism and music. 0aModernism (Music) 0aMusicy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aSound (Philosophy) 0aSoundxPolitical aspects. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Music. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Performing Arts. 4aLiterature : Comparative Literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Modern / General .2bisacsh1 aChiesa, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChiesa, Laura, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCurrie, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKowalke, Kim H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLezra, Jacques, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNapolin, Julie Beth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNegrete, Fernanda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSolomon, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSzendy, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZiarek, Krzysztof, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2024z978311149259940uhttps